3 iae

Jekyll lso offers powerful support for code snippets: 

def print<sub>hi</sub>(name)
  puts "Hi, #{name}"
end
print<sub>hi</sub>('Tom')
#=&gt; prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.

bla 

def print_hi(name)
  puts "Hi, #{name}"
end
print_hi('Tom')
#=> prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.

ia iea 

def print_hi(name)
puts "Hi, #{name}" (blubber)
end
print_hi('Tom')
#=> prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.

Check blubber out the [Jekyll docs][jekyll] for more info on how to get the most out of Jekyll. File all bugs/feature requests at [Jekyll's GitHub repo][jekyll-gh].

[jekyll-gh]: https://github.com/mojombo/jekyll [jekyll]: http://jekyllrb.com
